@startuml
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor white
}

frame "Kodelister" as KodelisterFrame <<folder>> {
  class Format #C<<codelist>>{ 
   Ukjent format = av/0\nRen tekst = x-fmt/111 \nTIFF versjon 6 = fmt/353\nPDF/A 1a - ISO 19005-1:2005=fmt/95\n PDF/A 1b -ISO 19005-1:2005=fmt/354\nXML=fmt/101\nJPEG=fmt/42\nSOSI=av/1\nMPEG-2=x-fmt/386\nMP3=fmt/134\nPNG=fmt/11

 } 

note right of Format : Codelist for file formats used in digital preservation systems like Arkivverket's e-Ark solution. The codes follow PRONOM identification scheme where 'fmt/' indicates formal registration while others may be internal or provisional identifiers.\nThe list includes both common office document types such as various versions of Adobe Portable Document Format along side multimedia containers including Moving Picture Experts Group standards alongside audio compression algorithms developed by Fraunhofer IIS among other specialized geospatial data exchange protocols defined under Norwegian mapping authority guidelines etcetera...


@enduml
